rcon
------------------------------------------
rcon is a command line application that can be used as a Source RCON client. It
will send commands to the given server, and print the reply to stdout.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.2.0-1
  libglib2.0_0-2.54.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  bash-completion-devel-2.7-1
  binutils-2.36.1-2
  check-0.15.2-1
  cmake-3.20.0-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-10.2.0-1
  libglib2.0-devel-2.54.3-1
  ninja-1.10.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/n0la/rcon

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/n0la/rcon/archive/0.6.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack rcon-0.6-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./rcon-0.6-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/rcon-0.6-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/rcon-0.6-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(rcon)
  /usr/bin/rcon.exe
  /usr/share/bash-completion/completions/rcon
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/rcon.README
  /usr/share/doc/rcon/LICENCE
  /usr/share/doc/rcon/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man1/rcon.1.gz

